We have reiterated the prior year’s recommendations that:

All Accountable Officers strictly remit their daily collections to Municipal Treasurer as required under Section 29 of the Manual of NGAS, Volume I; 

 Management institute mechanism or policy that there will be no new set /pads of accountable forms to be issued unless previously issued are already used-up and corresponding amount collected are reported and remitted. Therefore, part of this policy should include among others a reconciliation of the RCD of the AOS with the log book where issuances for Accountable Forms (AFs) are recorded;


 A certification by the AOs that all AFs issued to them are already used and the amount of collections remitted;

 Enhance the existing set of internal control measures of the LGU on the area of monitoring Accountable Forms issuances and its corresponding collection remittances;

 Management instill in the minds of the AOs that it will institute disciplinary actions against them if warranted that they have deliberately delayed revenue collection remittances. 

Relieve the Accountable Officers who continually delaying remittances of his/her collections.

