We have recommended that the management should strictly observe the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 in granting of cash advances. Extra effort should be exerted for the immediate settlement/liquidation of the cash advances especially those granted to elected officials. Issue demand letters in case officials/employees were not able to liquidate immediately their cash advances, if not possible, the following remedial measures maybe resorted to:

 Withhold the salaries and/or other benefits as provided for under Section    5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 and/or;

Appropriate  administrative and  criminal actions against the official/employee should be undertaken for the liquidation of their cash advances;

No granting of additional cash advances to official/employee unless their previous cash advances were liquidated and limit the grant of cash advance to elected officials for their travelling expenses and allowances only.

We have recommended that management:

Exercise prudence in the use of limited cash resources and stop the practice of incurring obligations when the disbursements thereof exceed fifty percent (50%) of the uncollected estimated revenues accruing to such local fund in addition to the actual collections pursuant to Section 337 of RA 7160;

Utilize the budget as a tool in maximizing the use of government funds. Program the expenditures appropriately in line with the Municipal Government’s short-term objectives;

The Local Finance Committee and other officials concerned to use the Daily Cash Flow Analysis in monitoring cash flows and outflow to ensure that sufficient cash is available to meet cash obligations as they fall due that monies held in trust be used only for intended purpose.

Management exercise prudence in spending for essential priority  programs and observe austerity measures in some of its activities and  projects until the cash deficit is fully controlled.

Strictly enforce the collection of taxes due to the municipality for it to be able to augment its dwindling resources and design strategies to ensure that what is due to the municipality can be collected for it to be able to undertake its operation in normal conditions.
